		<description>TIER 2 - Medieval
>>> Optimal	Economy
>> Suitable	Construction
X Inadvisable	Bladed Weapons
			
Tools Recommended: Any (cheap)

Wrought iron is your mostly-pure form of iron, meaning it has a very low carbon content. It's ductile (malleable) and be easily banged into shape, and that's it's greatest perk. This means the finished product may be easily bent. It's best used for fast construction, cheap tools, and as an intermediate material to produce blister steel or wootz steel. It can be made into weapons and armor by heat-treating to harden the face and edges, but still is only marginally effective.</description>
